1.  WHAT WE ARE BUILDING
Brain is Charles's personal AI operating system. It runs locally on Ubuntu Linux and ties together voice, vision, memory, web automation, file control, and multiple AI providers into one unified stack. Think of it like a personal Jarvis — but real, local, and fully under Charles's control.

This is not a chatbot. This is an agent operating system with:
    • A reasoning brain that thinks, remembers, and acts
    • Eyes (vision module) that can see the screen
    • Ears and a voice (wake word, STT, TTS)
    • Hands (keyboard/mouse automation via bridge)
    • A bug hunter that monitors and self-repairs
    • A bridge to n8n for workflow automation
    • A memory system with short-term, long-term, and layered storage

Charles built the first version of this system (called Odin) from scratch over 3 months with zero prior coding experience. It was destroyed by malware. This is the rebuild — cleaner, modular, Ubuntu-native.

